convert2openatom.f90:
This script converts wavefunctions generated by Quantum Espresso to states files for OpenAtom.
It requires qexml module in quantum espresso package.
To compile this script, place this script in PP/src directory, and add below two lines inside of the Makefile:

convert2openatom.x: ../../Modules/qexml.o convert2openatom.o
	$(LD) $(LDFLAGS) -o $@ convert2openatom.o ../../Modules/qexml.o $(QEOBJS) $(LIBOBJS)

Run the executable within the working directory, 
e.g., the same directory where the <prefix>.save/ directory is located.

EXAMPLE:
<YOUR_QE_DIRECTORY>/PP/src/convert2openatom.x < inputFile

See in.convert for the input file example




Addition:
convert2openatom_2.f90 : new converter for just comparison with openatom k point calculations.
This code calls setkevec3d_sm_kpt subroutine (from openatom)





